1/* $NetBSD: tegra.h,v 1.2 2018/08/27 04:58:30 riastradh Exp $ */
2
3#ifndef __NVKM_DEVICE_TEGRA_H__
4#define __NVKM_DEVICE_TEGRA_H__
5#include <core/device.h>
6#include <core/mm.h>
7
8struct nvkm_device_tegra {
9 const struct nvkm_device_tegra_func *func;
10 struct nvkm_device device;
11 struct platform_device *pdev;
12 int irq;
13
14 struct reset_control *rst;
15 struct clk *clk;
16 struct clk *clk_pwr;
17
18 struct regulator *vdd;
19
20 struct {
21 /*
22 * Protects accesses to mm from subsystems
23 */
24 struct mutex mutex;
25
26 struct nvkm_mm mm;
27 struct iommu_domain *domain;
28 unsigned long pgshift;
29 } iommu;
30
31 int gpu_speedo;
32};
33
34struct nvkm_device_tegra_func {
35 /*
36 * If an IOMMU is used, indicates which address bit will trigger a
37 * IOMMU translation when set (when this bit is not set, IOMMU is
38 * bypassed). A value of 0 means an IOMMU is never used.
39 */
40 u8 iommu_bit;
41};
42
43int nvkm_device_tegra_new(const struct nvkm_device_tegra_func *,
44 struct platform_device *,
45 const char *cfg, const char *dbg,
46 bool detect, bool mmio, u64 subdev_mask,
47 struct nvkm_device **);
48#endif
